dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, spot heights, and gradient tints.  Five classes of railways and five classes of roads are shown.  Covers area west from Legenfeld, Germany to Kralupy nad Vltavou, Czech Republic to the east, and north from Mittweida, Germany to Lázně Kynžvart (Königswart), Czech Republic to the south. Chemnitz roughly at upper left of center portion of sheet.  Sheet N.51, Chemnitz from series originally issued in various editions by Great Britain, War Office, Geographical Section, General Staff, No. 4346.  For use by War and Navy Department Agencies only. Not for sale or distribution..  Military grid.  Nord de Guerre Zone Grid ... Spheroid, Du Plessis..  Cataloging agency's copy overprinted with 4 coordinate scale circles with center points located roughly at E 12°53ʹ/N 50°44ʹ ; E 13°53ʹ/N 50°46ʹ ; E 13°53ʹ/N 50°16ʹ ; E 12°53ʹ/N 50°16ʹ.  IXA.  Heights in metres..  Certain main spot heights are indicated by a white tab to improve legibility..  Includes legend, Incidence of grid letters diagrams, Convergence for corners of this sheet diagram, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Grid data: Nord de Guerre Grid, Index to adjoining sheets, index to corresponding 1:100,000 scale sheets, Conversion table, Authorities, and Glossary. Also includes printer's color control bar in upper margin.  5/44SL..
dct_isPartOf_sm: Field Maps of Colonel Roland T. Fenton
